Good food, great service, reasonable prices.
My only complaint is that, like many other places that THINK they serve Chicago-style deep-dish pizza, they don't.
What they claim is deep-dish is, in fact, just thick crust pizza - a loaf of bread with ingredients - far removed from what you get on Wabash Street in Chicago.
Chicago deep-dish is baked in a pan, but the crust is THIN.
It's the ingredients that make it a meal-on-a-slice.
Did it taste good?
Yes.
Would I have it again?
Sure, it was flavorful.
But if you are expecting TRUE deep-dish pizza, this isn't it.

